race.comment: BELAURA STAR (2) trialled well and then raced as the favourite at Belmont on debut and did a good job beaten just 1.3L. The extra metres suit and he won't have to improve much to take this out. WHITE HOT (9) won a trial but was well out of the market in an Open 3 at Ascot on debut and needed the run. She jumps from an inside gate today, and Pike is a key jockey switch. Quick improvement is on the cards. COSMIC TREAT (6) resumes and is well placed with the 2kg claim. Has trialled and shown enough to be a chance. FUNKY BOY (4) debuts with the blinkers on. Has been well educated and won his latest trial. Keep safe with Chris Parnham booked. ALEBRIJE (10) was only beaten 2.5L at Belmont on debut, and she's sure to build on that. Draws to get every chance and she will carry just 53kg with the claimer engaged.
